      '## The Security Industry Has a Coverage Problem',
      'There are over 400 million small and medium-sized businesses worldwide. They run on cloud servers, handle customer data, and process payments. They are the backbone of the global economy. And virtually none of them have real cybersecurity.',
      'This is not because they do not care. It is because the entire security industry was built for a different customer.',
      '## Built for the Fortune 500, Ignored by Everyone Else',
      'CrowdStrike, Palo Alto, SentinelOne -- these are excellent products. They are also designed for enterprises with dedicated security teams, six-figure budgets, and months-long procurement cycles. A five-person startup running a single VPS on DigitalOcean is not their customer. Never was.',
